78:["$","p","p-14",{"children":"The robotics sector is at an inflection point driven by AI, sensor cost reduction, and foundation models:"}]
79:["$","ul","ul-32",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Foundation model era"}],": Single pre-trained policies handling many tasks, reducing per-task engineering cost by 10–100×."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Humanoid proliferation"}],": 2026–2030 likely sees scaling from thousands to hundreds of thousands of units; initially in controlled manufacturing, then expanding."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Democratization"}],": Lerobot, Octo, and open-source stacks enable university and startup R&D without proprietary middleware."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Human-robot teams"}],": Complementary roles — robots handle precision, repetition, hazard; humans handle ambiguity, creativity, and social interaction."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Cost reduction"}],": Cobot arm costs dropped from $50K (2015) to $15–20K (2025); continued decline will expand SME adoption dramatically."]}],"\n"]}]
